{"title":"The even weirder new Hope-Lotus track bike has a split seatpost and serrated fork","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hope-lotus-track-bike-team-gb-2023","date":1690550710000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hope-lotus-track-bike-team-gb-2023\">The even weirder new Hope-Lotus track bike has a split seatpost and serrated fork</a></p>\n\n<p>Team GB’s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hope-team-gb-track-bike-available-now-starting-at-15550\" target=\"_blank\">Hope-Lotus track bike</a> has received some wild updates that will debut at the Glasgow World Championships in August, ahead of the 2024 Paris Olympics. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"693\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-970x693.jpg\" alt=\"Hope Lotus Paris 2024 track bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-970x693.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-300x214.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-768x549.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-1536x1097.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-2048x1463.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-120x86.jpg 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-350x250.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-750x536.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-1140x814.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-1-190x136.jpg 190w\" /><figcaption>Alex Whitehead/SWpix</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The HBT frame, originally made for the Tokyo games, took a unique approach to aerodynamic design and featured a wide-armed fork and seatstays. The idea was to match the bike to the slipstream of the rider’s legs to reduce the overall drag. The result was a love-it-or-hate-it design but it’s hard to argue with the results as the GB track team cleaned up, winning seven medals in 2020 and topping the event medal table. </p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/filament-track-bike\">Could this foam-filled £7,250 track bike rival the Team GB Hope HB.T?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uci-road-cycling-world-championships-route-tv-guide-all-you-need-to-know\">Glasgow UCI Cycling World Championships 2023: Key information</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/lotus-110-bike\">In pictures: Lotus’ classic bikes</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Hope Lotus Paris 2024 track bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-3.jpg 1239w\" /><figcaption>Alex Whitehead/SWpix</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The second iteration of the bike apparently features small tweaks to the frame but the biggest changes are to the components. The fork now uses a serrated trailing edge, which Lotus says was inspired by fighter jet designs and claims that it helps further smooth the airflow around the rider.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lotus says the fork is made from the same high grade carbon as used in its Evija hypercar, balancing strength and a light weight.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Hope Lotus Paris 2024 track bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-2.jpg 1238w\" /><figcaption>Alex Whitehead/SWpix</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While the fork/handlebar integration has also been revamped to reduce drag, the tiny, aggressive handlebars of the previous bike have been replaced in favour of a more adaptable setup. The team says it wanted to provide riders with more options in order to promote a more sustainable aero riding position for some of the longer races.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Hope Lotus Paris 2024 track bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-5.jpg 1239w\" /><figcaption>Alex Whitehead/SWpix</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The seatpost is the wackiest feature, however. The 3D printed piece is made by Renishaw and incorporates a large hole that looks like a cross between a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/trek-madone-review\" target=\"_blank\">Trek IsoFlow</a> and a Dyson fan. While similar designs on the road may also focus on compliance, the key focus on the track is reducing drag and air turbulence. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"Hope Lotus Paris 2024 track bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-1140x759.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Lotus_hope_GB_track_bike_paris-6.jpg 1240w\" /><figcaption>Alex Whitehead/SWpix</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Renishaw hasn’t provided any figures to demonstrate the improvement but says over 150 hours of wind-tunnel and advanced computational fluid dynamics (CFD) testing went into creating the final build. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Shell logos on the chainrings are a blunt touch – see our piece on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/what-is-greenwashing-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">greenwashing in cycling</a> – but it will be great to see the rest of the bike in action in Glasgow and further along at the Paris Olympics next year. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hope-lotus-track-bike-team-gb-2023\">The even weirder new Hope-Lotus track bike has a split seatpost and serrated fork</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"0378d24344d9fc5837813d02bc1fae5a9aeb0af2bb29341bce0f8d85779d70b5","category":"Cycling"}